                "rating": 5,
                "relative_time_description": "10 months ago",
                "text": "A wonderful resource. My recent appointments were the first time I accessed this type of support and I was nervous about it. To my relief, everyone on site is extremely warm and welcoming. They create a space that feels community oriented, respectful, and non-judgmental. The space feels homey and is well organized. There is a good range of food options that accommodate  my vegetarianism. The review that mentions that it takes a bit to get in for a shopping appointment is accurate (think it was 2 weeks from my contact with the organization to when I was able to get in), however they do have emergency bags available if there are immediate needs - you'll just not have the choice of items available during shopping appointments. Their hours are accommodating to those who work business hours, which is a rarity in this area it seems. I leave my appointments feeling empowered and respected. Can't recommend highly enough!",
